Subject: Re: [T2] Re: Squeal/whistle in engine

> That is a good point Bob.. some heads have the step cast into them,, some
> don't and should... so you need to install the shims between the head and
> the barrel..

Don't put ANYTHING between the head and the barrel. Anything you put
there weakens the seal. Which is why VW themselves recommended a
direct head to cylinder fitting.

Check out this pic:
http://www.donimages.com/guacamolebus/photos/photo.php?id=214

Those were on ONE head off a 79. And those heads had never been
machined since new. Good step, good lip, etc.

